Architecture plan for Issue #101: Fix homepage hero typo "Lastest" → "Latest"

Project structure:
- Next.js App Router frontend lives under src/app with public routes grouped in src/app/(public).
- Shared UI components live under src/components; global styling is in src/app/globals.css and Tailwind config.
- Server/database helpers live under src/lib; Prisma schema/migrations are under prisma/.
- Rust Axum API lives under src-rs and is coordinated with the Next app by scripts/start-coordinated.mjs.

Issue dependency plan:
- Issue #101 is standalone and has no functional dependencies.
- Scope is limited to homepage display copy. Search the public homepage route and any extracted hero component for the misspelled string "Lastest" and replace only that typo with "Latest".

Key design decisions:
- Do not alter application architecture, data model, API routes, authentication, storage, or deployment scripts for this text-only change.
- Keep the existing product branding/copy style intact; only correct the specified typo.
- Verify with targeted grep plus the normal Next/TypeScript checks as appropriate for a small UI copy change.
